  "timeframe": "1M",
  "market_context": "On 11/1/2023, NQ formed a consolidation range on the 1-minute chart with an aggressive manipulation leg down sweeping the range low before displacing back into the range, setting up a bullish Box setup scenario.",
  "key_observation": "Rather than entering immediately on the retest of the range deviation, the analyst waited for an order block formation (down-close candle into the fair value gap followed by a closure above it) to confirm the box setup before taking the long entry.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify the consolidation range by marking the lowest bodies of the accumulation phase.",
    "Step 2: Wait for the manipulation leg — an aggressive move out of and back into the range — to confirm the box setup.",
    "Step 3: Note that the standard box entry would be a retest of the range low with stop on the manipulation low.",
    "Step 4: Instead of entering immediately, wait for a down-close candle to trade into the fair value gap area for order block formation.",
    "Step 5: Look for a close above that down-close candle to validate it as a bullish order block.",
    "Step 6: Enter long at the order block with stop on the manipulation low.",
    "Step 7: Project the manipulation leg using standard deviations to set targets at the previous high and the first standard deviation fair value gap confluence.",
    "Step 8: Confirm price reaches the projected target."
  ],
  "outcome": "Target hit — price reached the previous high and first standard deviation projection that aligned with the fair value gap.",
  "lessons": "Combining the Box setup (AMD) with an order block confirmation provides higher-probability entries than entering immediately on the deviation retest. Waiting for a CISD/order block validation tightens risk and confirms intent before committing to the trade.",
